Product vision:
Smart Lighting Ecosystem that gradually regulates lighting at home depending on the time of the day and day of the week to optimize user circadian rhythms. 

Project goal:
The project goal is to build an automated smart lighting IoT ecosystem with a few purposes in mind:
1. Improve user's sleep quality. 
2. Learn new technology stack. 
3. Use legacy hardware devices as sensors and displays.

Proof of Concept:
- Software: Home Assistant Software
- Hardware: macOS, Windows PC + Zigbee USB Dongle + Oracle VirtualBox + 1 light bulb
- System goal: manually change light temperature, keep that setting when power is off. 

MVP v1:
- Software: Home Assistant Software
- Hardware: Windows PC + Zigbee USB Dongle + 1 light bulb (1 room) + Smart Light Sensor
- System goals: automatically change light temperature gradually depending on the real time light sensor readings.


MVP v2:
- Software: Zigbee2MQTT, Node-RED
- Hardware: Dedicated Linux station + Zigbee USB Dongle + 1 light bulbs (1 room) + Smart Light Sensor
- System goals: Automatically change light temperature gradually depending on the real time light sensor readings or depending on projected height of the sun.
